The paper discusses the application of social network analysis and information retrieval techniques for discovering relations among names, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and data mining (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of co-occurrence graphs, which could also place it under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with proper names, which could potentially fall under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
